4. A short one-line description of what the task does.
   Use these descriptions:
   - SequenceClassificationTask: assigns a single label to an input sequence.
   - MultiLabelClassificationTask: assigns multiple simultaneous labels to an input sequence.
   - NLITask: determines whether a hypothesis is entailed, contradicted, or neutral w.r.t. a premise.
   - NERTask: assigns named entity labels to each token in a sequence.
   - POSTaggingTask: assigns morphosyntactic tags to each token in a sequence.
   - FillMaskTask: predicts masked tokens in a sentence using masked language modelling.
   - ExtractiveQATask: extracts a verbatim answer span from a context passage.
   - CompletionTask: generates free-form text from a prompt using autoregressive LM.
   - MachineTranslationTask: translates text from a source language to a target language.
   - SummarizationTask: condenses a long text into a shorter summary.
   - DialogueTask: generates the next reply conditioned on a conversation history.
   - RagTask: retrieves relevant passages and generates a grounded answer.
   - AgentTask: plans and executes actions in a loop by calling external tools.
   - EmbeddingTask: encodes text into dense vectors in a semantic space.
   - RetrievalTask: retrieves the most relevant passages from an indexed knowledge base.
   - TopicModelingTask: discovers latent topics in a corpus without supervision.
   - ClusteringNLPTask: groups similar texts into clusters without predefined labels.
   - ASRTask: transcribes audio into text.
   - ASTTask: translates spoken audio directly into text in a target language.
   - TTSTask: synthesises audio from text.

Design requirements:
- Clean, minimal, professional — suitable for an internal dev tool
- Color-code the task branches:
  Discriminative → blue, Generative → green,
  Representation → purple, Audio → orange,
  Standalone (ExtractiveQATask, RetrievalTask,
  TopicModelingTask, ClusteringNLPTask, FillMaskTask) → gray
- The breadcrumb uses the same branch color
- No use case selected by default — show a placeholder message in
  the right panel ("Select a use case to see the associated task")
- Smooth transition when switching between use cases
- The search filters the list in real time as the user types
